| Topic                  | Required Inputs                              | Drafting Notes                                                                                  |
|------------------------|---------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Modification/Clarification | Section references; exact revised text     | Clearly state how sections are amended or clarified with precise citations                      |
| Additional Rights       | Right holders; scope; triggers               | Define conditions, limitations, timeframes, and remedies                                       |
| Exceptions/Waivers      | Baseline obligations; exception scope        | Limit exceptions narrowly, avoid broad implied waivers                                         |
| Confidentiality        | Disclosure permissions                        | Align with fund and investor requirements                                                      |
| Conditions             | Precedent or subsequent triggers             | Use objective criteria and specific deadlines                                                  |
| Duration               | End dates or triggering events                | Specify survival of key clauses                                                                |
| Conflict Hierarchy      | Conflicting terms                             | Side letter controls only on addressed matters                                                 |
| Dispute Resolution      | Forum; arbitration rules                       | Mirror primary agreement unless justified                                                      |
| Notices                | Addresses and methods                          | Incorporate primary agreement’s provisions unless changed                                     |

### Drafting Template

```text
SIDE LETTER AGREEMENT

This Side Letter Agreement (this "Side Letter") is entered into as of [Date] by and between [Party A] and [Party B] (each, a "Party" and collectively, the "Parties").

WHEREAS, the Parties are party to that certain [Primary Agreement Title], dated [Date] (the "Agreement");

WHEREAS, the Parties desire to modify, clarify, or supplement the Agreement as set forth below.

1. Modification/Clarification. Section [X] of the Agreement is hereby [amended/clarified] as follows: [insert replacement or addendum text].

2. Additional Rights. [Describe special rights, conditions, timeframes, and limits].

3. Confidentiality. [Set forth permitted disclosures and obligations regarding the Side Letter].

4. Term and Termination. [Specify duration and survival clauses].

5. Relationship to Agreement. Except as expressly set forth herein, the Agreement remains in full force and effect. In the event of conflict, this Side Letter controls solely as to matters addressed herein.

[Optional Clauses: Assignment; Notices; Entire Agreement and No Oral Modification; Severability; Waiver; Counterparts; Electronic Signature; No Third-Party Beneficiaries; Governing Law; Dispute Resolution.]

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have executed this Side Letter as of the date first written above.
```

### Quality Control Checklist

- [ ] Confirm all cross-references exactly match the primary agreement  
- [ ] Ensure defined terms align with or supplement the primary agreement  
- [ ] Verify changes do not exceed intended scope  
- [ ] Confirm all required consents and approvals are obtained  
- [ ] Ensure confidentiality terms align with disclosure obligations  
- [ ] Verify governing law and dispute resolution provisions are consistent or justified  
- [ ] Confirm signature blocks reflect correct authority and titles  

guidelines:
- Use defined terms and formatting consistent with the primary agreement  
- Keep modifications narrow and explicitly tied to stated sections  
- State side letter confidentiality and permitted recipients  
- Avoid altering rights of non-signatories without explicit consent  
- If primary agreement forbids side letter modifications, prepare a formal amendment instead  
- Align drafting with investor rights frameworks, MFN provisions, and fund reporting obligations in VC/PE deals  
- If selecting different governing law or dispute resolution, explain rationale in recitals or a dedicated clause  
